# --- full batch outputs (bulky, regenerable; the smoke_* outputs ARE committed as a
#     ready-to-view example) ---
results/
meta/
plots/
/results_summary.md

# --- logs / benchmark artifacts ---
*.log
bench_results.json

# --- python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/

# The synthetic test data (synthetic_geno.*, synthetic_clinical-*.tsv, synthetic_truth-*.tsv)
# IS committed on purpose — it is 100% RNG-generated, so mirroring the repo gives a
# ready-to-run example with no data-privacy concern.
#
# Guard against accidentally committing a REAL genotype fileset, while allowing the
# synthetic example through:
*.pgen
*.bed
*.bgen
!synthetic_geno.pgen
